Willie Fung https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Willie_Fung 0 Willie Fung (3 March 1896 – April 16, 1945) was a Chinese film actor who played supporting roles in 125 American films between 1922 and 1944. Born in Canton, China, Fung made his film debut in 1922 in Hurricane's Gal. The majority of his roles were in Westerns and dramas. Fung died of a coronary occlusion in Los Angeles, California on 16 April 1945 at the age of 49. He is buried in Angelus-Rosedale Cemetery in Los Angeles.
